import java.util.*;
class StringAndStringBuffer
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        String a = "a";
        String s = "";
        StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer();

        final int N = 10000;

        long t0 = System.currentTimeMillis();
        for( int i=0; i<N; i++) s+=a;
        long t1 = System.currentTimeMillis();
        for( int i=0; i<N; i++) sb.append(a);
        long t2 = System.currentTimeMillis();

        System.out.println(t1-t0); // 151
        System.out.println(t2-t1); // 1
    }
}

class TestStringMethod
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        String s = new String( "Hello World" );

        System.out.println( s.length() );
        // 11
        System.out.println( s.indexOf('o') ); 
        // 4
        System.out.println( s.indexOf("He") );
        // 0
        System.out.println( s.startsWith("He") );
        // true
        System.out.println( s.equals("Hello world") );
        // false
        System.out.println( s.equalsIgnoreCase("Hello world") );
        // true
        System.out.println( s.compareTo("Hello Java") );
        // 13
        System.out.println( s.charAt(1) );
        // e
        System.out.println( s.substring(0,2) );
        // He
        System.out.println( s.substring(2) );
        // llo Wolrd
        System.out.println( s.concat("!!!") );
        // Hello World!!!
        System.out.println( s.trim() );
        // Hello World
        System.out.println( s.toUpperCase() );
        // HELLO WORLD
        System.out.println( s.toLowerCase() );
        // hello world
        System.out.println( s.replace('o', 'x' ) );
        // Hellx Wxrld
        System.out.println( s );  //注意，s本身没有改变
        // Hello World
    }
}



import java.util.*;
class TestStringTokenizer
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer("this is a test", " ");
        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
            System.out.println(st.nextToken());
            /**
             * this
             * is
             * a
             * test
             */
        }
        st = new StringTokenizer("253,197,546", ",");
        double sum = 0;
        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
            sum += Double.parseDouble(st.nextToken());
        }
        System.out.println( sum ); // 996.0
    }
}
